parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at night.
symptoms: headlights go out and come back on
headlights remain off for extended periods
headlights turn on and off intermittently

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, oil leakage, and engine performance issues, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or engine damage.
symptoms: White smoke or steam coming out of the tailpipe

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Thermostat failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, loss of vehicle control, or accidents.
Oil line failure can cause oil leakage, leading to engine damage, loss of vehicle control, or accidents.
Vehicle fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injury, or death.
The failure of the front disc brakes can cause violent vibrations while braking, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: brakes fail to stop the vehicle
rotors and brake pads need to be replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to vibrate out of control or fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: ABS warning light comes on while driving
vehicle vibrates out of control when brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate out of control, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: accelerator pedal feels stuck to the floor
failure to respond to attempts to turn off speed control or press the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of sensors such as the HEGO (Heated Exhaust Gas Oxygen) and PFE (Pressure Feedback EGR) sensors can affect engine performance and potentially cause other issues.

Fuel line leaks can cause gasoline to leak into the vehicle, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially causing accidents or injuries. Additionally, fuel leaks can lead to fuel loss, decreased fuel efficiency, and engine performance issues.
symptoms: fuel leaks under the passenger door
fuel leaks around the rear of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair of recalled fuel system components can lead to continued fuel leaks, fire hazards, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: Fuel leaks persist after recall repair
fuel sending unit failure after recall repair
lack of parts for recall repair
